{"type":"text","timestamp":1775875192184,"sessionID":"ses_2859c9bcbffes4sOhzPY4OWWic","part":{"id":"prt_d7a68e985001g0iYr3u3wzBZ1l","messageID":"msg_d7a68c136001PxnDc2DWLueYiB","sessionID":"ses_2859c9bcbffes4sOhzPY4OWWic","type":"text","text":"I've successfully created the proposal.md file for AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/cmd/cli/proposal.md`.\n\nThe proposal includes:\n\n**Purpose**: Standardize and enhance the Kubernetes provider system for deploying AI agents to both standard Kubernetes and AgentCube CRD environments.\n\n**Scope**: \n- Unified provider interface (`BaseProvider`) with consistent method signatures\n- Two provider implementations: `KubernetesProvider` (Deployment + NodePort Service) and `AgentCubeProvider` (AgentRuntime CR)\n- Provider factory pattern for extensibility\n- Enhanced error handling with custom exceptions and retry mechanisms\n- Status monitoring with real-time tracking and event querying\n- Configuration management with validation and persistence\n- Plugin system for custom provider extensions\n\n**Impact Analysis**:\n- Backward compatibility preserved through adapter layer\n- Minimal performance impact with connection pooling and caching\n- No new external dependencies\n\n**Alternatives Considered**:\n1. Minimal changes (doesn't address core issues)\n2. Complete rewrite (high risk, long timeline)\n3. **Recommended**: Progressive enhancement (balanced approach)\n\nThe proposal includes a detailed 7-week implementation plan with specific deliverables, risk assessment, and success metrics.","time":{"start":1775875192182,"end":1775875192182}}}
